From: Peter Amiri <petera@pai.com>
Date: Sat, 18 Apr 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] fix(cfml): return exit 1 when expression execution fails

`lucli cfml '<expr>'` currently swallows CFML execution errors: the catch
block logs to stderr but falls through to `return result`, where `result`
is still `null`. picocli maps a null Object return to exit code 0, so every
failure reports success to callers (shells, CI, doctest harnesses).

Add `return 1;` in the catch so the command exits with a non-zero code on
any execution failure. The finally block still runs (Timer.stop), and the
null execution-result path is skipped because there's nothing meaningful
to expose programmatically on failure anyway.

---
 .../java/org/lucee/lucli/cli/commands/CfmlCommand.java         | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/src/main/java/org/lucee/lucli/cli/commands/CfmlCommand.java b/src/main/java/org/lucee/lucli/cli/commands/CfmlCommand.java
--- a/src/main/java/org/lucee/lucli/cli/commands/CfmlCommand.java
+++ b/src/main/java/org/lucee/lucli/cli/commands/CfmlCommand.java
@@ -65,10 +65,11 @@ public class CfmlCommand implements Callable<Object> {
             // We can capture output here if needed
             result = LuceeScriptEngine.getInstance().eval(cfmlCode);

         }
         catch (Exception e) {
             System.err.println("Error in cfml command: " + e.getMessage());
             LuCLI.debugStack(e);
+            return 1;
         }
         finally {
             Timer.stop("CFML Command Execution");
         }
